nodes.bodyText: What does this actually get used for?
I think it's the slot you spawn in.
Yea but the PR doesn’t reference it anywhere

Indeed. I just copied the stuff from the old GW branch and did not cross-check.
In ladder the map positions somehow work out of the box.
But if you have more than 2 players and you need sorting (left vs right or top vs bottom) you will somehow need to solve that.
So this would be the number of players when the lobby is full? I don't think the server implements it correctly yet. It'll be easy to fix though.
Yes, the autolobby starts the game if the number of expectedPlayers is connected. Until then you are in the connecting stage.
No. We still lack the team number and whatever the players argument does.
Team number and players are being sent now. The players argument is just a number that tells the lobby it should wait until that many players have joined before launching the game.
So u are argueing for removing it?
Can we add the numgames parameter as a dedicated field in this message too instead of passing it via args?
I would say yes why not
I decided not to do this for now
